<TITLE> Local government conference begins </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 5 (bdnews24.com)  A conference of elected representatives of local government institutions started at the National Parade Square in Dhaka Saturday. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed joined the conference as chief guest. Thousands of local government representatives from across the country joined the conference, chaired by LGRD and cooperatives adviser Anwarul Iqbal. In his speech, Fakhruddin mentioned the Election Commission's ongoing efforts to complete preparations for the elections, expected by the end of 2008. The CA also listed a series of steps to curb the spiralling prices of rice. His speech came amid the allegations of the government mishandling the situation of food prices. Local Government Division secretary Sheikh Khurshid Alam delivered the welcome address. The daylong conference aims at infusing dynamism into the local government institutions. A special committee submitted a report to the conference, detailing recommendations to strengthen local government institutions. Copies of the reportboth in Bangla and Englishwere distributed among the participants of the conference.
